The paper proposes an automated 3D medical image retrieval pipeline using deep convolutional neural networks for classification on 2D montage images. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the form of the proposed automated pipeline. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of retrieving whole brain CT scans from a cohort of traumatic brain injury patients.
